principalId.description: The object ID of the service principal object for your managed identity that is used to grant role-based access to an Azure resource.

PipelineJob.description: Pipeline Job definition: defines generic to MFE attributes.

bindings.description: Binding to represent relation between inputs, outputs and parameters

items.description: Binding Inputs/Outputs to ComponentJob Inputs/Outputs etc

additionalProperties.description: Job output definition container information on where to find job output/logs.

settings.description: Pipeline settings, for things like ContinueRunOnStepFailure etc.

failureThreshold.description: The number of failures to allow before returning an unhealthy status.

initialDelay.description: The delay before the first probe in ISO 8601 format.

period.description: The length of time between probes in ISO 8601 format.

successThreshold.description: The number of successful probes before returning a healthy status.

timeout.description: The probe timeout in ISO 8601 format.

ReferenceType.description: Enum to determine which reference method to use for an asset.

keyType.description: Specification for which type of key to generate. Primary or Secondary.

keyValue.description: The value the key is set to.

tags.description: Tag dictionary. Tags can be added, removed, and updated.

instanceCount.description: Optional number of instances or nodes used by the compute target.

instanceType.description: Optional type of VM used as supported by the compute target.

ResourceIdentity.description: Service identity associated with a resource.

principalId.description: Client ID that is used when authenticating.

tenantId.description: AAD Tenant where this identity lives.

userAssignedIdentities.description: Dictionary of the user assigned identities, key is ARM resource ID of the UAI.

ResourceIdentityAssignment.description: Defines values for a ResourceIdentity's type.

SecretsType.description: Enum to determine the datastore secrets type.

resourceUrl.description: Resource the service principal has access to.

tenantId.description: ID of the tenant to which the service principal belongs.

default.description: Gets or sets the default capacity.

scaleType.description: Gets or sets the type of the scale.

SkuResource.description: Fulfills ARM Contract requirement to list all available SKUS for a resource.

capacity.description: Gets or sets the Sku Capacity.

SkuResourceArmPaginatedResult.description: A paginated list of SkuResource entities.

nextLink.description: The link to the next page of SkuResource objects. If null, there are no additional pages.

value.description: An array of objects of type SkuResource.

SkuSetting.description: SkuSetting fulfills the need for stripped down SKU info in ARM contract.

name.description: The name of the SKU. Ex - P3. It is typically a letter+number code.

tier.description: This field is required to be implemented by the Resource Provider if the service has more than one tier, but is not required on a PUT.

earlyTermination.description: Early termination policies enable canceling poor-performing runs before they complete

identity.description:
Identity configuration. If set, this should be one of AmlToken, ManagedIdentity or null.
Defaults to AmlToken if null.

inputs.description: Mapping of input data bindings used in the job.

outputs.description: Mapping of output data bindings used in the job.

additionalProperties.description: Job output definition container information on where to find job output/logs.

samplingAlgorithm.description: Type of the hyperparameter sampling algorithms

searchSpace.description: A dictionary containing each parameter and its distribution. The dictionary key is the name of the parameter

maxInstances.description: The maximum number of instances that the deployment can scale to. The quota will be reserved for max_instances.

minInstances.description: The minimum number of instances to always be present.

pollingInterval.description: The polling interval in ISO 8691 format. Only supports duration with precision as low as Seconds.

targetUtilizationPercentage.description: Target CPU usage for the autoscaler.

workerCount.description: Number of workers. If not specified, will default to the instance count.

codeId.description: ARM resource ID of the code asset.

command.description: The command to execute on startup of the job. eg. "python train.py"

distribution.description: Distribution configuration of the job. If set, this should be one of Mpi, Tensorflow, PyTorch, or null.

environmentId.description: The ARM resource ID of the Environment specification for the job.

environmentVariables.description: Environment variables included in the job.

resources.description: Compute Resource configuration for the job.

TruncationSelectionPolicy.description: Defines an early termination policy that cancels a given percentage of runs at each evaluation interval.

truncationPercentage.description: The percentage of runs to cancel at each evaluation interval.

UserAssignedIdentityMeta.description: User assigned identities associated with a resource.

clientId.description: Aka application ID, a unique identifier generated by Azure AD that is tied to an application and service principal during its initial provisioning.

principalId.description: The object ID of the service principal object for your managed identity that is used to grant role-based access to an Azure resource.
